<div class="col-md-12">
    <p>
        The Most Popular Destination Of Eastern Dooars Is The Buxa Forests. Being A Tiger Reserve, There Is Restriction In Tourist Movement In The Area. Tourists May Visit A Number Of Destinations Within The Buxa Forests Such As Raimatang, Buxa Fort, Jayanti, Lepchakha And Others. Coochbihar The Erstwhile Kingdom Of The Cooch Dynasty Also Falls In The Area.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">EASTERN DOOARS (BUXA TIGER RESERVE & BUXA DUAR ALTITUDE OF 2600 Ft.)</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Touching One State Boundary And One International Boundary Lays The 'Buxa Tiger Reserve' In The Eastern Dooars Of West Bengal.
        This Tiger Reserve Is Located Near Alipurduar, Well Connected By Train And Road.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Is Tiger, Leopard (Black Panther Also), Elephant, Clouded Leopard, Himalayan Black Bear, Barking Deer, Gaur, Pangolin, And Python. Buxa Duar Is Famous For Its Prison Fort. The Park Was Declared As National Park Since 1992 And The Name Buxa Was Derived From A Fort Used For Detainees During Freedom Movement Of India. A Trek Of Nearly 14 Kilometers Will Take Tourist Near It. Mahakal A Religious Center Is 6 Kilometers Trek From Jayanti And Can Be Done In A Day.
    </p>
    <b>Circuit Routing </b>
    <p>
        Chilapata, Rasikbill Is Close To Cooch Behar And Can Be A Days Excursion.Cooch Behar, Jaldapara, Lataguri, Buxa Forms A Circuit Worth Visiting
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-danger">OTHER ATTRACTION IN & AROUND</h4>
    <h4 class="text-info">Raimatang, Nimati</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        At A Distance Of 45 Km From Alipurduar, Raimatang Is A Nice Place To Enjoy The Beauty Of Nature. Nimati Is 17 Km Away From Alipurduar.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Scenic Beauty Is The Point Of Attraction Of These Places.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Jayanti</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        This Forest Village Is Around 30 Km Away From Alipurduar Town Of Jalpaiguri District And Connected By Road. One Can Also Move Here From Rajabhatkhawa.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Jayanti Is Famous For Its Rich Variety Of Wild Life And Exotic Scenic Beauty. A Stalakite Cave Popularly Known As 'Jayanti Mahakal' And 'Pookri Pahar' Are Well Known Destinations From Jayanti.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Rajabhatkhawa</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Rajabhatkhawa Is 15 Km Away From Alipurduar Town And Located In Between Alipurduar And Jayanti. This Place Is Connected Both By Road And Train From Alipurduar And Siliguri.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Variety Of Important Flora And Fauna Exists In This Area. Nature Interpretation Centre And Tiger Rescue Centre Are Points Of Interest Of This Place.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Rasikbill </h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        This Is A Water Body Stretching In The Extreme End Of Buxa Tiger Reserve. This Water Body Is In The Periphery Of The Forest. It Is Very Close To Alipurduar Nearly An Hour And Half Drive By Car. It Is The Eastern End Of Buxa Tiger Reserve Near Assam Border.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        A Nature Interpretation Centers With Leopards, Birds, Deer's, Crocodile And Other Animals Are Rescued And Treated Here.Bill In Bengali Literally Means A Water Body. This Place Is Ideal For Angling With Permission, Birding, Boating Or Even Sitting Idle In Any Side Of The Banks Of The Water Body Is Many Of The Pastime Tourists Can Enjoy. Diversified Variety Of Avifauna Like Ibis, Spoonbill, Mynas, Orioles, Parakeets, Kingfisher, Parrots, Owl, Flycatchers, Partridges, Cormorants, Storks And Woodpeckers Are Some Of The Species That Can Be Spotted. 
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Cooch Behar </h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Cooch Behar Is Only 3 – 3 ½ Hour’s Drive From Siliguri. Buxa Tiger Reserve, Chilapata, Rasikbill Is Close To Cooch Behar And Can Be A Days Excursion.Cooch Behar, Jaldapara, Lataguri, Buxa Forms A Circuit Worth Visiting.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Cooch Behar Is A Historical Town And Is Home To Many A Religious Place, Park, Lakes And Wildlife In Vicinity. The Main Attraction Is The Famous Cooch Behar Palace With Museum, Historical Artifact And The Garden Attached Surrounding It. 
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Lepchakha</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Lepchakha Is A Small Drukpa Village On A Hilltop Inside The Buxa Tiger Reserve. The Village Is Located Close To Bhutan, The Areal Distance Not Being More Than 2 To 3 Kms. There Is A Boarder Outpost Of The Security Agencies Here. The Village Has A Very Small Population Of About A Hundred People.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        The Main Attraction Of Lepchakha Is The View From The Hilltop. There Is A Large Ground Where You Can Seat On A Bench And Be Mesmerised By The View Of Dooars In Front. Almost The Entire Buxa Forest Area Is Visible From Here Including Every Nook And Corner. As Many As Seven Rivers Flowing Through The Buxa Forest Can Be Seen From Here. To Your Extreme Left You Can See River Sankosh Followed By River Raidak, Jayanti, Bala And Others. You Can See Alipurduar Town, Jayanti Riverbed, Santalabari And The Entire Green Cover In Front Of You. Turn Around And Behind You Are The Hills Of Mahakal, Chuna Bhatti And Rovers Point Which Together Makes For A Great Trek.
    </p>
